

Release Beta 0.41
* now you can move the Petri Dish with the mouse! (Thanks to Zaskar)
* simplifying Ruby to Bash (mainly because this year Gaston is not in the project)
* some cleanups of older files in lib

=========================================================================

Release Beta 0.40
* WARNING: release 0.40 is NOT backward compatible because important changes in rules and microorganisms interface. 
* time decoupling: change the time simulation to one MO per moment
* reproduction: now by mitosis ( no more sexual reproductions ;-) )
* MO interface: new methods and signatures (mitosis, move, update); internal energy, position and colony ID;
* GUI: new 3D!!!
* automatic backups for: results.yml results.txt petri.h
* misc: almost all petri.h and colony are new; more translations in source and documentarion, updated examples in MOs, etc...

=========================================================================

Release RB-0.30
* Only one building of comvida: with all microorganisms and selection of them by command line
* Incorporation doxygen: documentation system for the source code
* General translations: root documents, directories and names of generated files
* IMPORTANT for microorganisms developers: removed distNutri from defs.h, now you can get the nutrient distribution by agar.distNutri()

